cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.CL, cs.CV, cs.NE 

The paper proposes a hybrid inference algorithm that combines search-based and data-driven methods using a neural network. This suggests that the paper is likely to belong to the Machine Learning (cs.LG) and Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI) sub-categories. The paper also evaluates the algorithm on two tasks related to natural language processing (symbolic program parsing) and computer vision (probabilistic matrix decomposition), indicating that it may also belong to the Computational Linguistics (cs.CL), Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition (cs.CV), and Neural and Evolutionary Computing (cs.NE) sub-categories.
